{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3253,"text":"(Video) Newscaster: There's a large path\nof destruction here in town."},{"time":6595,"text":"... pulling trees from the ground,\nshattering windows,"},{"time":9537,"text":"taking the roofs off of homes ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12377,"text":"Caitria O'Neill: That was me"},{"time":14436,"text":"in front of our house in Monson,\nMassachusetts last June."},{"time":17817,"text":"After an EF3 tornado ripped\nstraight through our town"},{"time":21182,"text":"and took parts of our roof off,"},{"time":22685,"text":"I decided to stay in Massachusetts,"},{"time":24754,"text":"instead of pursuing the master's program"},{"time":26683,"text":"I had moved my boxes\nhome that afternoon for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29906,"text":"Morgan O'Neill: So, on June 1,\nwe weren't disaster experts,"},{"time":32761,"text":"but on June 3, we started faking it."},{"time":34859,"text":"This experience changed our lives,"},{"time":36889,"text":"and now we're trying\nto change the experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39350,"text":"CO: So, tornadoes\ndon't happen in Massachusetts,"},{"time":41819,"text":"and I was cleverly standing in the front\nyard when one came over the hill."},{"time":45344,"text":"After a lamppost flew by, my family\nand I sprinted into the basement."},{"time":48668,"text":"Trees were thrown against the house,\nthe windows exploded."},{"time":51588,"text":"When we finally got out the back door,"},{"time":53481,"text":"transformers were burning in the street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55775,"text":"MO: I was here in Boston."},{"time":57236,"text":"I'm a PhD student at MIT,"},{"time":58977,"text":"and I happen to study atmospheric science."},{"time":61683,"text":"Actually, it gets weirder --"},{"time":63055,"text":"I was in the museum of science\nat the time the tornado hit,"},{"time":66373,"text":"playing with the tornado display --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68228,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":69430,"text":"so I missed her call."},{"time":70605,"text":"I get a call from Caitria, hear the news,\nand start tracking the radar online"},{"time":74373,"text":"to call the family back when another\nsupercell was forming in their area."},{"time":77827,"text":"I drove home late that night\nwith batteries and ice."},{"time":80292,"text":"We live across the street\nfrom a historic church"},{"time":82629,"text":"that had lost its very\niconic steeple in the storm."},{"time":85318,"text":"It had become a community\ngathering place overnight."},{"time":87807,"text":"The town hall and the police department\nhad also suffered direct hits,"},{"time":91135,"text":"and so people wanting to help\nor needing information went to the church."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94789,"text":"CO: We walked to the church because\nwe heard they had hot meals,"},{"time":97848,"text":"but when we arrived, we found problems."},{"time":99744,"text":"There were a couple large,\nsweaty men with chainsaws"},{"time":102213,"text":"standing in the center of the church,\nbut nobody knew where to send them"},{"time":105647,"text":"because no one knew the extent\nof the damage yet."},{"time":107970,"text":"As we watched, they became\nfrustrated and left"},{"time":110145,"text":"to go find somebody to help on their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112124,"text":"MO: So we started organizing.\nWhy? It had to be done."},{"time":114807,"text":"We found Pastor Bob and offered to give\nthe response some infrastructure."},{"time":118274,"text":"And then, armed with just\ntwo laptops and one air card,"},{"time":121470,"text":"we built a recovery machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125488,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":128106,"text":"CO: That was a tornado, and everyone's\nheading to the church"},{"time":131138,"text":"to drop things off and volunteer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132828,"text":"MO: Everyone's donating clothing."},{"time":134432,"text":"We should inventory\nthe donations piling up here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136850,"text":"CO: And we need a hotline.\nCan you make a Google Voice number?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139811,"text":"MO: Sure. And we need to tell people\nwhat not to bring."},{"time":142417,"text":"I'll make a Facebook account.\nCan you print flyers?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144854,"text":"CO: Yeah, but we don't even know\nwhat houses are accepting help."},{"time":147934,"text":"We need to canvas and send out volunteers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149963,"text":"MO: We need to tell people\nwhat not to bring."},{"time":152100,"text":"Hey, there's a news truck. I'll tell them."},{"time":154128,"text":"CO: You got my number off the news?\nWe don't need more freezers!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":157176,"text":"(Together) MO: Insurance won't cover it?\nCO: Juice boxes coming in an hour?"},{"time":161204,"text":"Together: Someone get me Post-its!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162852,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":163877,"text":"CO: And then the rest of the community\nfigured out that we had answers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167578,"text":"MO: I can donate three water heaters,\nbut someone needs to come pick them up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171243,"text":"CO: My car is in my living room!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172814,"text":"MO: My boyscout troop\nwould like to rebuild 12 mailboxes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175663,"text":"CO: My puppy is missing and insurance\ndoesn't cover chimneys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178557,"text":"MO: My church group of 50\nwould like housing and meals for a week"},{"time":181644,"text":"while we repair properties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182998,"text":"CO: You sent me to that place\non Washington Street yesterday,"},{"time":185935,"text":"and now I'm covered in poison ivy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187613,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188736,"text":"So this is what filled our days."},{"time":190526,"text":"We had to learn\nhow to answer questions quickly"},{"time":192764,"text":"and to solve problems in a minute or less;"},{"time":195038,"text":"otherwise, something\nmore urgent would come up,"},{"time":197262,"text":"and it wouldn't get done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198620,"text":"MO: We didn't get our authority\nfrom the board of selectmen"},{"time":201451,"text":"or the emergency management\ndirector or the United Way."},{"time":204331,"text":"We just started answering questions\nand making decisions"},{"time":206981,"text":"because someone -- anyone -- had to."},{"time":209640,"text":"And why not me? I'm a campaign organizer."},{"time":212019,"text":"I'm good at Facebook."},{"time":213211,"text":"And there's two of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214513,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216083,"text":"CO: The point is, if there's a flood\nor a fire or a hurricane,"},{"time":219635,"text":"you, or somebody like you,"},{"time":221420,"text":"are going to step up\nand start organizing things."},{"time":224055,"text":"The other point is that it is hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226356,"text":"MO: Lying on the ground\nafter another 17-hour day,"},{"time":229071,"text":"Caitria and I would empty our pockets"},{"time":230902,"text":"and try to place dozens of scraps\nof paper into context --"},{"time":233690,"text":"all bits of information\nthat had to be remembered and matched"},{"time":236580,"text":"in order to help someone."},{"time":237832,"text":"After another day\nand a shower at the shelter,"},{"time":240015,"text":"we realized it shouldn't be this hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242212,"text":"CO: In a country like ours\nwhere we breathe Wi-Fi,"},{"time":245081,"text":"leveraging technology for a faster\nrecovery should be a no-brainer."},{"time":248636,"text":"Systems like the ones\nthat we were creating on the fly"},{"time":251204,"text":"could exist ahead of time."},{"time":252521,"text":"And if some community member\nis in this organizing position"},{"time":256074,"text":"in every area after every disaster,"},{"time":258644,"text":"these tools should exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261049,"text":"MO: So, we decided to build them:"},{"time":262980,"text":"a recovery in a box, something that\ncould be deployed after every disaster"},{"time":266514,"text":"by any local organizer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268437,"text":"CO: I decided to stay in the country,\ngive up the master's in Moscow"},{"time":271844,"text":"and to work full-time to make this happen."},{"time":273932,"text":"In the course of the past year,"},{"time":275449,"text":"we've become experts in the field\nof community-powered disaster recovery."},{"time":278933,"text":"And there are three main problems\nthat we've observed"},{"time":281441,"text":"with the way things work currently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283496,"text":"MO: The tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284671,"text":"Large aid organizations are exceptional\nat bringing massive resources to bear"},{"time":288630,"text":"after a disaster,"},{"time":289817,"text":"but they often fulfill very specific\nmissions, and then they leave."},{"time":293256,"text":"This leaves local residents to deal with\nthe thousands of spontaneous volunteers,"},{"time":297498,"text":"thousands of donations,"},{"time":298681,"text":"and all with no training and no tools."},{"time":300712,"text":"So they use Post-its or Excel or Facebook."},{"time":303864,"text":"But none of these tools allow you\nto value high-priority information"},{"time":307102,"text":"amidst all of the photos and well-wishes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309595,"text":"CO: The timing."},{"time":310929,"text":"Disaster relief is essentially\na backwards political campaign."},{"time":314121,"text":"In a political campaign,\nyou start with no interest"},{"time":316867,"text":"and no capacity to turn that into action."},{"time":319073,"text":"You build both gradually,"},{"time":320308,"text":"until a moment of peak mobilization\nat the time of the election."},{"time":323483,"text":"In a disaster, however,\nyou start with all of the interest"},{"time":326242,"text":"and none of the capacity."},{"time":327582,"text":"And you've only got about seven days"},{"time":329678,"text":"to capture 50 percent of all\nof the Web searches that will ever be made"},{"time":333141,"text":"to help your area."},{"time":334580,"text":"Then some sporting event happens,"},{"time":336191,"text":"and you've got only the resources\nthat you've collected thus far"},{"time":339231,"text":"to meet the next five years\nof recovery needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342121,"text":"This is the slide for Katrina."},{"time":345047,"text":"This is the curve for Joplin."},{"time":347510,"text":"And this is the curve\nfor the Dallas tornadoes in April,"},{"time":350317,"text":"where we deployed software."},{"time":351995,"text":"There's a gap here."},{"time":353693,"text":"Affected households have to wait\nfor the insurance adjuster to visit"},{"time":356926,"text":"before they can start accepting help\non their properties."},{"time":359688,"text":"And you've only got about four days\nof interest in Dallas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363829,"text":"MO: Data."},{"time":365184,"text":"Data is inherently unsexy,"},{"time":367042,"text":"but it can jump-start an area's recovery."},{"time":369288,"text":"FEMA and the state will pay\n85 percent of the cost"},{"time":372329,"text":"of a federally-declared disaster,"},{"time":373948,"text":"leaving the town to pay\nthe last 15 percent of the bill."},{"time":376613,"text":"Now that expense can be huge,"},{"time":378246,"text":"but if the town can mobilize X amount\nof volunteers for Y hours,"},{"time":382224,"text":"the dollar value of that labor used\ngoes toward the town's contribution."},{"time":387089,"text":"But who knows that?"},{"time":388782,"text":"Now try to imagine\nthe sinking feeling you get"},{"time":391028,"text":"when you've just sent out 2,000 volunteers\nand you can't prove it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395622,"text":"CO: These are three problems\nwith a common solution."},{"time":398083,"text":"If we can get the right tools\nat the right time"},{"time":401136,"text":"to the people who will inevitably step up"},{"time":403126,"text":"and start putting\ntheir communities back together,"},{"time":405505,"text":"we can create new standards\nin disaster recovery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408231,"text":"MO: We needed canvasing tools,\ndonations databasing,"},{"time":411189,"text":"needs reporting, remote volunteer access,"},{"time":414203,"text":"all in an easy-to-use website."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416074,"text":"CO: And we needed help."},{"time":417535,"text":"Alvin, our software engineer\nand co-founder, has built these tools."},{"time":420723,"text":"Chris and Bill have volunteered their time\nto use operations and partnerships."},{"time":424818,"text":"And we've been flying into disaster areas\nsince this past January,"},{"time":428334,"text":"setting up software, training residents"},{"time":430707,"text":"and licensing the software to areas\nthat are preparing for disasters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434969,"text":"MO: One of our first launches\nwas after the Dallas tornadoes"},{"time":437819,"text":"this past April."},{"time":438994,"text":"We flew into a town\nthat had a static, outdated website"},{"time":441648,"text":"and a frenetic Facebook feed,\ntrying to structure the response,"},{"time":444638,"text":"and we launched our platform."},{"time":446050,"text":"All of the interest came\nin the first four days,"},{"time":448316,"text":"but by the time they lost the news cycle,"},{"time":450310,"text":"that's when the needs came in,"},{"time":451771,"text":"yet they had this massive resource\nof what people were able to give"},{"time":454965,"text":"and they've been able to meet\nthe needs of their residents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457753,"text":"CO: So it's working,\nbut it could be better."},{"time":459833,"text":"Emergency preparedness is a big deal\nin disaster recovery"},{"time":462535,"text":"because it makes towns safer\nand more resilient."},{"time":464808,"text":"Imagine if we could have\nthese systems ready to go in a place"},{"time":467723,"text":"before a disaster."},{"time":469972,"text":"So that's what we're working on."},{"time":471804,"text":"We're working on getting the software\nto places so people expect it,"},{"time":475037,"text":"so people know how to use it"},{"time":476402,"text":"and so it can be filled ahead of time"},{"time":478208,"text":"with that micro-information\nthat drives recovery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480614,"text":"MO: It's not rocket science."},{"time":482471,"text":"These tools are obvious\nand people want them."},{"time":484714,"text":"In our hometown,\nwe trained a half-dozen residents"},{"time":487166,"text":"to run these Web tools on their own,"},{"time":488912,"text":"because Caitria and I\nlive here, in Boston."},{"time":491124,"text":"They took to it immediately,\nand now they are forces of nature."},{"time":494124,"text":"There are over three volunteer groups\nworking almost every day,"},{"time":497103,"text":"and have been since June 1 of last year,"},{"time":499135,"text":"to make sure these residents get what\nthey need and get back in their homes."},{"time":502742,"text":"They have hotlines\nand spreadsheets and data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505089,"text":"CO: And that makes a difference."},{"time":507203,"text":"June 1 this year marked the one-year\nanniversary of the Monson tornado,"},{"time":511081,"text":"and our community's never been\nmore connected or more empowered."},{"time":514398,"text":"We've been able to see the same\ntransformation in Texas and in Alabama."},{"time":518654,"text":"Because it doesn't take Harvard or MIT"},{"time":520501,"text":"to fly in and fix problems\nafter a disaster;"},{"time":522590,"text":"it takes a local."},{"time":523938,"text":"No matter how good an aid organization\nis at what they do,"},{"time":526817,"text":"they eventually have to go home."},{"time":528516,"text":"But if you give locals the tools,"},{"time":530754,"text":"if you show them\nwhat they can do to recover,"},{"time":533583,"text":"they become experts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537007,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":538055,"text":"MO: All right. Let's go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539231,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}